    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About CoQ10 Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is CoQ10 and why is it important?</summary>
      <p>CoQ10 is a naturally occurring antioxidant in every cell, with highest concentrations in the heart. It is essential for mitochondrial ATP production (cellular energy) and protects cell membranes from oxidative damage. Levels decline naturally after age 30 and are depleted by statin medications, making supplementation important for older adults and statin users.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the difference between ubiquinone and ubiquinol?</summary>
      <p>Ubiquinone is the oxidized form (most common, most studied). Ubiquinol is the reduced, active form. The body converts between them. Ubiquinol may achieve higher blood levels per dose, especially in older adults. Both are effective. Ubiquinol is 2-3x more expensive.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Should I take CoQ10 if I am on statins?</summary>
      <p>Statins reduce CoQ10 production by up to 40%. A 2018 meta-analysis found CoQ10 supplementation reduced statin-associated muscle symptoms significantly. Many cardiologists recommend 100-200mg daily for statin users. Consult your prescribing physician before adding CoQ10.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What dosage of CoQ10 is effective?</summary>
      <p>100-200mg daily for general health and statin support. 200-300mg for heart failure. Up to 1,200mg in research settings. CoQ10 is fat-soluble — take with a fat-containing meal for 2-3x better absorption. Most gummies provide 100-200mg per serving.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Does CoQ10 improve energy levels?</summary>
      <p>In individuals with depleted levels (older adults, statin users, chronic fatigue), supplementation can meaningfully improve energy and reduce fatigue. A 2015 RCT found 200mg daily reduced fatigue scores significantly. If levels are already adequate, the energy boost may be minimal.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Is CoQ10 good for heart health?</summary>
      <p>The Q-SYMBIO trial (2014) found 300mg daily for 2 years reduced major cardiac events by 43% in heart failure patients. CoQ10 supports heart function through energy production (the heart has the highest metabolic demand) and antioxidant protection of cardiac cells and LDL cholesterol.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>When should I take CoQ10 gummies?</summary>
      <p>With a fat-containing meal for optimal absorption. Morning or lunch preferred — some users report mild insomnia with evening dosing. If taking statins, consider taking CoQ10 at the same time for routine consistency.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are CoQ10 gummies safe?</summary>
      <p>Excellent safety profile at doses up to 1,200mg daily. Mild GI symptoms (nausea, diarrhea) in ~1% of users. May reduce warfarin effectiveness and enhance blood pressure medication effects. Those on blood thinners or BP meds should consult their physician.</p>
    </details>

